Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    ###############################################
    # Basic OS packages
    ###############################################
    apt-get update
    # Python, pip, ping (set-uid root binary) and parallel utilities
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        iputils-ping \
        parallel \
        ca-certificates

    # Clean apt cache to keep the image lean
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    ###############################################
    # Python packages (pytest for task validation)
    ###############################################
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    ###############################################
    # Prepare initial filesystem state
    ###############################################
    # Ensure /home/user exists with open permissions
    mkdir -p /home/user
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Create the required inventory file with exact content
    cat > /home/user/iot_targets.csv <<'EOF'
device01,127.0.0.1
device02,10.255.255.1
EOF
    # Make sure the file ends with a newline and is world-readable
    echo >> /home/user/iot_targets.csv
    chmod 644 /home/user/iot_targets.csv

    ###############################################
    # Do NOT create /home/user/logs – must be absent
    ###############################################

%labels
    Author edge-computing-task-builder
    Description "Environment prepared for IoT gateway reachability task – contains initial inventory and pytest"

%help
    This Apptainer image provides the initial state for the IoT gateway
    reachability task.  It contains:
      • Ubuntu 22.04 base system
      • python3, pip, pytest
      • iputils-ping (set-uid root inside the container for ICMP)
      • GNU parallel
      • The inventory file at /home/user/iot_targets.csv

    The /home/user/logs directory is intentionally absent.